  "text": "If an entity develops what is called a karma in an incarnation, is there then programming that sometimes occurs so that he will experience catalysts that will enable him to get to a point of forgiveness, thereby alleviating the karma. I am Ra. This is in a general correct, however, both the self and any involved other self may at any time through the process of understanding, acceptance, and forgiveness ameliorate these patterns. This is true at any point in an incarnative pattern. Thus, one who has set in motion an action may forgive itself and never again make that error. This also breaks or stops what you call karma.",
